This is my 2021 @irisguitar OG model built in Burlington, VT by the luthiers behind @circlestrings and @fairbanksguitars. I’m in love with my Circle Strings OM so I was very intrigued when Adam and the team started producing the Iris guitars as affordable, high-end instruments built by luthiers in the USA. I played one at the @artisanguitarshow in spring 2020 and got this one in beginning of 2021. 

It is very responsive, woody, light, bare-bones, and soulful with a very basic finish and appointments. 

The Iris is so inspiring to me that I recorded an entire record (Crazy Grace) using only this guitar.  I was also inspired by my friend @jordan.tice to limit myself to standard tuning and push myself to come up with compelling arrangements for every song on Crazy Grace without relying on alternate tunings.

The OG has an Adirondack spruce top and Honduran mahogany back and sides, a 25-inch scale, a nut with of 1 3/4”, and a cool logo by @vibrosonic!

I get asked often about what I do to my nails. Here you go: I grow the natural nail out and then have a local salon apply a few layers of UV-cured gel on top of the natural nail. I have this done every four weeks or so. After many years of doing them myself with super glue, etc, this is the best option I’ve found - I love the tone, durability, and convenience. What do you do?

This is my 2001 @martinguitar OM-15. It’s an all-mahogany guitar with no binding and simple dot inlays. I had to search for a while to find the OM version of Martin’s 15 series and eventually found this one on Craigslist in New Jersey. The OM is less common than the OOO, D, and OO models. It’s all original except the previous owner added titanium bridge pins (🤷‍♂️) and I added Waverly tuners. It was my main guitar before I got the @circlestrings. Someone dropped it a few years ago so it has a repaired crack on the side but it plays and sound perfect. 

It has a very woody, dry sound that is great for fingerstyle and light strumming. 

Someone was borrowing it for a while and I’m glad to have it back in my hands - I’ll post some videos with it soon!
